beer.beer_description: Over 35 years ago Phil Sexton and the brewers at Matilda Bay introduced Australians to the wonders of wheat beer, the delicate, exotic flavours combined with that characteristically creamy and full mouthfeel. Wind forward the clock and we’re at it again, this is a wheat beer but not like you remember. Championing all Australian wheat and Australian Eclipse hops this bright and fresh brew is equal parts hazy and lively. Tangerine flesh, Seville orange, and silky full wheat, with subtle bitterness and a crisp tight finish. No need for a slice of citrus with this one.
